Job Description

The Senior-Level Data Scientist is a pivotal member of our team, leveraging cutting-edge data analysis, statistical modeling, and algorithm development skills. This role is essential for providing deep insights and driving informed decisions that support our organization's strategic goals.

Key Responsibilities


Data Analysis & Insights:
Utilize exploratory and descriptive data analysis techniques on complex datasets to uncover patterns, trends, and actionable insights.
Apply advanced statistical methods to interpret results, enabling data-driven recommendations for strategic decisions.
Predictive Modeling & Analytics:
Engineer and deploy predictive models and algorithms using state-of-the-art machine learning and AI techniques.
Continuously evaluate and refine model performance, ensuring high accuracy and reliability in predictive insights.
Communication & Collaboration:
Distill complex analytical findings into clear, understandable insights for non-technical stakeholders.
Work closely with cross-functional teams, ensuring seamless integration of data science capabilities into business operations and strategy.
Innovation & Algorithm Development:
Innovate and construct bespoke algorithms tailored to solve specific organizational challenges.
Stay at the forefront of data science research, applying the latest findings and technologies to enhance our analytical framework.

Job Requirements


Bachelor's or Master's degree in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or a related field;
At least 3-5 years of hands-on experience in data science, with a proven track record of successful projects;
Proficient in Python is a must;
Strong skills in Microsoft SQL is a must;
Familiar with R programming;
Skilled in using data science and machine learning libraries (e.g., Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch);
Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, Matplotlib, Seaborn);
Experience with AWS EC2 and Linux: ability to configure and manage Linux-based virtual machines in AWS Cloud environments;
Proficiency in shell scripting and Linux command-line tools for system monitoring and administration in the cloud. managing Linux AWS Virtual Machines using Putty commands;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work with complex datasets and derive meaningful insights;
Exceptional communication abilities, capable of translating complex technical findings into clear, actionable insights for both technical and non-technical audiences;
Demonstrated ability to work effectively in collaborative, interdisciplinary teams, with a commitment to achieving shared goals.


Desirable Skills:


Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure) and understanding of their data services;
Knowledge of advanced statistical techniques and their application in predictive modeling;
Familiarity with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark).


